     <br/>
     <br/>
     <b>
      <br/>
      Memory Aid:
     </b>
     Think of a teacher clapping her
hands to get the student's attention.
     <br/>
     <b>
      Other meanings
     </b>
     :  "Academic"
     <br/>
     <b>
      Handshape
     </b>
     :  loose "flat" hands. (Or even "5" hands, but 
	the fingers tend to be together.)
     <br/>
     <b>
      Location
     </b>
     : In the neutral signing space in front of the body
     <br/>
     <b>
      Orientation
     </b>
     : Right hand faces down.  Left hand faces up.
     <br/>
     <b>
      Movement
     </b>
     :  "Clap" the hands together twice.  (Do it
quietly. No need to make noise. Duh.)
     <br/>
     <hr/>
     <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
      Note: There is a separate and specific sign for "Deaf School" that initializes 
the sign "SCHOOL" with "i" handshapes.
